2015 programmer&rsquo;s guide:
 Kernel itself makes only minor use of capabilities; Kernel is not currently compiled with a capability-aware compiler; kernel threads do not have full capability-register-file state in their own PCBs.  A hardcoded kernel capability1:
/* * Definition for a highly privileged kernel capability able to name the * entire address space, and suitable to derive all other kernel-related * capabilities from, including sealing capabilities. */ #define	CHERI_CAP_KERN_PERMS	\ 	(CHERI_PERMS_SWALL | CHERI_PERMS_HWALL) #define	CHERI_CAP_KERN_BASE	0x0 #define	CHERI_CAP_KERN_LENGTH	0xffffffffffffffff #define	CHERI_CAP_KERN_OFFSET	0x0  cherireg.
